# HCDE 530 Week 2 Project — Cursor context

## Project

Course exercise: read survey responses from CSV, summarize word counts in Python, and optionally present data in `dashboard.html`. Treat `demo_responses.csv` as the source of truth for participant text.

## Directory structure

Update this tree whenever you add, remove, or rename **tracked project files** or create/remove **top-level folders** (not `.git` internals).

```
HCDE 530 Week 2 Project/
├── .cursorrules          # This file — agent & editor context
├── CONTEXT.md            # Human project context, run instructions, code section map
├── week2.md              # Week 2 reflection — Competency 2 (code literacy & documentation)
├── .gitignore            # Python/macOS noise (e.g. .DS_Store, venv)
├── count_words.py        # App reviews: load reviews.csv, print min/max/avg word stats
├── demo_responses.csv    # Survey data (participant_id, role, response)
├── demo_word_count.py    # Loads CSV, prints per-row + summary word stats
├── dashboard.html        # Static dashboard; embeds CSV-derived JSON for file:// use
└── reviews.csv           # Fictional app reviews (review_id, text) for count_words.py
```

## Maintaining `.cursorrules`

- After any layout change above, **edit the Directory structure section** so it matches the repo. If `CONTEXT.md` is added or renamed, update here and keep `CONTEXT.md` aligned with real behavior.
- If new file types appear (e.g. `requirements.txt`, `scripts/`), add a one-line comment in the tree explaining purpose.
- Do not list `.git/` contents in the tree.

## Python (`demo_word_count.py` and similar)

- Use the standard library (`csv`); no extra dependencies unless the user asks.
- Open CSV with `encoding="utf-8"` and `newline=""` when using `csv.reader` / `DictReader`.
- **Word count** should match the existing script: `len(text.split())` on the response string (whitespace-separated tokens). Keep behavior consistent with the dashboard if both exist.
- Prefer clear, instructional code suitable for a class assignment; avoid over-abstracting.

## Data files

- Survey CSV: column names must match the header: `participant_id`, `role`, `response`.
- App reviews CSV (`reviews.csv`): `review_id`, `text` — used only by `count_words.py`.
- If `demo_responses.csv` changes and `dashboard.html` embeds JSON, regenerate or update the embedded data so the dashboard stays in sync.

## `dashboard.html`

- Self-contained static HTML/CSS/JS is fine; no build step required.
- Preserve offline use (embedded data or documented need for a local server if using `fetch`).

## Scope

- Keep edits limited to this project folder unless the user expands scope.
- Do not commit `.DS_Store` (already in `.gitignore`).
